## The index command
bcftools index input.vcf.gz

## The input has to be either bgzipped or a bcf. The resulting index, unlike a reference genome index, will be a binary file and not human-readable 
# Region coding
An entire chromosome:
bcftools view -r chr1 input.vcf.gz
Just a single position:
bcftools view -r chr2:1643 input.vcf.gz
A range of positions on a single chromosome: (most common)
bcftools view -r chr3:1-1000 input.vcf.gz
